<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,284,905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[499,615,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[264,382,1750,1774]" captionTargetBox="[266,1313,925,1750]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[258,1317,890,1750]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Scatella bullacosta Cresson. Male. 1. Wing; 2. epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 3. epandrium, cerci and surstyli, lateral view; 4. aedeagus, anterior view; 5. aedeagus, lateral view; 6. gonite, anterior view; 7. gonite, lateral view; 8. phallapodeme, anterior view. 9. Female genitalia, ventral receptacle; 10. abdominal sternites and cerci." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171139/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Figs. 
<number box="[567,615,284,310]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="5.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="2.0">2–8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Cercus thick and short; surstylus without inner incision at tip in posterior view; gonite narrow at base; phallapodeme moderately long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,284,905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Female. Body length 
<quantity box="[563,656,359,385]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[813,907,359,385]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
. Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1128,1252,359,385]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[264,382,1750,1774]" captionTargetBox="[266,1313,925,1750]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[258,1317,890,1750]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Scatella bullacosta Cresson. Male. 1. Wing; 2. epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 3. epandrium, cerci and surstyli, lateral view; 4. aedeagus, anterior view; 5. aedeagus, lateral view; 6. gonite, anterior view; 7. gonite, lateral view; 8. phallapodeme, anterior view. 9. Female genitalia, ventral receptacle; 10. abdominal sternites and cerci." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171139/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Figs. 
<number box="[1194,1252,359,385]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
</figureCitation>
).Ventral receptacle long, tube­like, about 
<number box="[694,731,399,425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="4.5">4.5</number>
times as long as wide.
</paragraph>
